    • ETL & FCC Listed: Lumary smart disk lights are ETL-Listed and FCC compliant, ensuring they are energy efficient and reliable
    • J-Box or Recessed Can Installation: The Lumary flush mount ceiling light is only 1.77" thick and can be installed into any 3.5/4 inch J-Box or 5/6 inch recessed can, perfect for new construction and retrofit lighting projects in spaces like entrance, porch, kitchen, living room, basement, garage and more
    • Brightness & RGBWW Adjustable: Smart disk ceiling downlights support warm white and cool white adjustments from 2700K to 6500K, offering 16 million RGB colors.     • Multiple Control Ways: Download the "Lumary" APP to connect and enjoy intelligent control (NOTE: Our flush mount smart light only supports 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi). Additionally, it can also be controlled remotely through Alexa, Google Assistant, and Siri
    • Explore Smart Lighting Possibilities: The smart flush mount ceiling lights change color with music or game sounds via the APP. Set schedules to automatically turn the LED disk lights on and off based on your daily routine. Create groups of Lumary LED retrofit lights in your home through the APP for unified control, making it easier to manage your lighting

        • Dave
          5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
          Great Product
          Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2025
          1.
          I purchased 6 lights for my outdoor screen room. I've had them for about 4 months now and I'm very happy with them. You will need a good wifi connection to run these lights. I have a wifi extender in the ceiling of the screen room, if I didn't I don't think... See more
          I purchased 6 lights for my outdoor screen room. I've had them for about 4 months now and I'm very happy with them. You will need a good wifi connection to run these lights. I have a wifi extender in the ceiling of the screen room, if I didn't I don't think these would work. Connecting to the wifi was fairly easy, you will need to download an app to control the lights. The lights can be controlled individually or as a group, you will need to create a group in the app. I like this feature because I can control them individually. If I'm cooking I can have a bright light over the grill and have the rest of the lights off, or on a low dim color. I can have the lights on over the table and off over by the TV. You can share control of the lights to multiple devices. On the app you can name the lights individually, I simply named them by location. This is a great feature so I know which light is which. The app has preset setting "buttons". It has 8 that you can customize to any setting you want, you can also create a name for these settings. I set up the 8 preset features and named them by basically the color I have them set to, for example "Light Blue", "Low White", "Bright White", ect. During Christmas time I had half of the lights set to red and half set to green, I named that setting "Christmas". The app also has 30 various pre set light settings that you cannot change. There are color flashing modes where the lights will change colors, you can pick the colors, the speed of the change, and if it fades or flashes. The lights can also change to the beat of music. The app has a color "wheel" that you use to set the light to basically any color you want. It has a dimmer "slider" to set them to any brightness. I have on occasion had a light not respond when I tried to change the color or turn it off. After a minute or so the problem corrected its self, I believe that is a wifi issue not an issue with the light fixture. The only thing I don't like about them is the color of the fixture. I have them against a pure white ceiling and they are not a white color, they almost look dirty.
